Package: AHBPCEPredR
Type: Package
Title: AHB Pulmonary Clinical Exercise Predictions in R
Version: 0.4.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Tom", "Alexander", email = "thomas.alexander3@va.gov", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Shobhik", "Chakraborty", email = "shobhik.chakraborty@va.gov", role = "aut")
    )
Description: A comprehensive collection of functions for cardiopulmonary exercise testing (CPET) 
    calculations and pulmonary function predictions used in clinical practice. This package 
    provides standardized implementations of widely-used prediction equations including:
    FRIEND VO2 predictions (Silva et al. 2020), ventilatory calculations, maximum heart rate 
    predictions (Arena et al. 2016), O2 pulse calculations (Ross et al. 2020), GLI 2021 
    Global (race-neutral) spirometry reference equations (Bowerman et al. 2023) for FEV1, FVC, 
    and FEV1/FVC ratio, GLI 2021 lung volume equations for FRC, TLC, RV, RV/TLC, ERV, IC, 
    and VC, and GLI 2017 DLCO equations for DLCO (TLCO), KCO, and VA with predicted values, 
    lower/upper limits of normal, z-scores, and percent predicted calculations. Includes Miller 
    correction for hemoglobin adjustment of DLCO. Includes quality control functions for clinical 
    exercise testing and pulmonary function testing. Designed for use by pulmonary function 
    laboratories and exercise physiology clinics to ensure consistent and accurate calculations 
    in clinical practice.
